==> version control system :-
--> version control system is a software which will track the changes of source code and save them as multiple version
whenever developer modifies the code.
--> It is divides into 3 types:-
** Local version control system
** Centralized version control system
** Distributed version control system

Local version control system:-
It is software which will save all the version of the code in local system of a developer.

==> Drawback of Local version control system:-
--> If Local system fails then developer loose the data.
--> No collaboration.
Software :- Revision Control System & Source Control System.


==> Centralized version control system:-
--> Centralized version control system Which will save all the version of the code in a Centralized place
where all the developers can collaborate with each others.
Software:- SubVersion & ConCurrent Version Control System.

==> Drawback of Centralized version control system:-
--> Internet Mandatory.
--> If central server is failed then developer loose the code.

Distributed version control system:-
--> Distributed version control system which will save all the version of the code in both version control system.

Software:- GIT(2005) , Mercurial ,  Bazaar

GIT: Global information Tracker.(Introduced:- Linus Torvalds)
--> It is open sources .

