==> Undoing changes:-
--> command:-
** git checkout / git restore
** git reset
** git revert
** git rm (remove)
** git reflog

--> git checkout or restore is used toh remove the changes to in working directory.
** git checkout filename
** git restore filename
** git checkout .
** git restore .

--> if u want to back the file from staging area to working directory we can use
** git reset filename

--> To delete the latest commit undo to get a file to local repo. to staging area.
** git reset --soft Head~1

-->  To delete the latest commit undo to get a file to local repo. to Working directory.
** git reset --mixed Head~1

--> To delete the latest commit undo to remove the modification of the file.
** git reset --hard Head~1

